commText: Rohit and Ishan Kishan are at the crease. Rohit is on strike. Khaleel Ahmed will open the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Rohit, no run, fuller length delivery and a hint of shape back into the right-hander, Rohit leans well forward on the defensive push
Khaleel Ahmed to Rohit, 1 run, Khaleel keeps it full and well wide of off, draws Rohit into the drive and the edge rolls down to third man for a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, uppish, fuller length delivery and well wide of off - Kishan leans into the slice and slices it uppishly, behind square on the off-side for a single

Khaleel Ahmed to Rohit, 1 run, Khaleel keeps it full and angles one across the right-hander, Rohit drives away from his body, plays with an open face and squirts it behind square on the off-side for a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, short, wide and four, width on offer and Kishan doesn't miss out - gets on top of the bounce and then punches it square past point, no need to run for those
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, no run, on a good length and just outside off - Kishan leans across into the drive and inner halves it to mid-on
Ishant to share the new ball, a slip in place
Ishant Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Ishant to Rohit, wide, a gentle start from Ishant, pushes one full and down leg, called as a wide

Ishant to Rohit, FOUR, cheeky and four, on a good length and well wide of off - Rohit gets down low, uses the pace on the ball and then laps it backward of square on the on-side, bounces away to the ropes
Ishant to Rohit, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Rohit - pitched up by Ishant, the right-hander leaned into the lofted drive and gets enough to clear mid-off, bounces away to the ropes
Ishant to Rohit, 5 wides, this is a horror start from Ishant - pushes one full and down leg, kept going away from Pant's reach and he can only palm it away to the ropes on the dive
Ishant to Rohit, no run, much better from Ishant - short of a good length and holding its line outside off, draws Rohit into the push and beats him on the outside edge
Ishant to Rohit, no run, Ishant shortens the length and gets it to straighten with the angle - has Rohit playing away from hid body and beats him on the outside edge
Ishant to Rohit, no run, on a good length and just outside off - a good stride forward on the defensive push
Ishant to Rohit, no run, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, Rohit throws his bat on the drive and misses, four consecutive dot balls from Ishant, still a 14-run over
Rohit vs Ishant in IPL (before today) Balls: 40 Runs: 48 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 16.0 SR: 120.0

Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, 2 runs, whipped, fuller length delivery on the pads, Kishan gets inside the line and then flicks it over mid-wicket, came off the lower half and slows down near the ropes
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, no run, Khaleel shortens the length outside off, punched off the back-foot to cover-point
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, no run, fraction fuller and just outside off - Kishan bends his front-leg and then drives with an open face, straight to the fielder at backward point
Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, clubbed, back of a length and just outside off - Kishan swivels across, gets on top of the bounce and then pulls it wide of mid-on, bounces away to the ropes

Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, 2 runs, fuller length delivery and well wide of off - Kishan went hard on the drive and mistimed it over mid-off, comes back for the second. Was in the air, but he had got enough to clear the infield

Khaleel Ahmed to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, hammered, a low full-toss as Khaleel went for the yorker - Kishan jams his bat down and drills it back over the bowler's head, races away to the straight boundary, another expensive over, 12 came off it
Jhye Richardson, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
J Richardson to Rohit, no run, short of a length and into the body, Rohit was swivelling across on the pull and cops a blow on his box
J Richardson to Rohit, SIX, crunched, on a good length and just outside off - Rohit is quick to spot the length, a shuffle across and then plays the pick-up shovel, sending it soaring into the stands

J Richardson to Rohit, SIX, back-to-back sixes for Rohit - fraction fuller and just outside off, Rohit shuffles across, gets inside the line and then shovels it over backward square leg, he's off and running now
J Richardson to Rohit, no run, on a good length and just outside off, Rohit tries to run it down towards third man and gets an under-edge that bounces through to the keeper
J Richardson to Rohit, 1 run, the slower ball from Richardson, Rohit backed away and then went hard on the drive, mistiming it to the left of mid-off for a single

J Richardson to Ishan Kishan, no run, shout for LBW, but the umpire reckons it pitched outside leg, might've been going over as well - nipped back in and caught Kishan in the crease, striking him high on the pad
Time for spin and it's Axar
Axar Patel, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Axar to Rohit, SIX, .. and he's picked for a first-ball six - pushed through flatter and down leg - Rohit gets inside the line, used the pace on the ball and then swept it over backward square leg for a maximum
Axar to Rohit, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, worked down wide of mid-on for a single
Axar to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, worked in front of square on the on-side for a single

Axar to Rohit, FOUR, nicely played, tossed up on middle - Rohit shuffles a long way and then clears square leg with the sweep - the fielder in the deep is very square, the ball slows down, but it does have enough to beat his dive and trickle into the ropes
Axar to Rohit, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle, nudged past square leg for a single
Axar to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, flicked past square leg for a single
It's Lalit Yadav now

Over summary 1-5 - Ishan gets going with a four - Rohit takes Ishant for consecutive fours, but wides galore as MI get 14 off the over - Rohit smashes Jhye for consecutive sixes - Axar goes for 14 in his 1st over
Lalit Yadav, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Lalit Yadav to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, tossed up on off, driven down to long-off for a single
Lalit, from round the wicket

Lalit Yadav to Rohit, FOUR, clubbed, flighted delivery and angling across the right-hander - Rohit clears his front leg and then hammers the drive back over the bowler's head, bounces away to the ropes
Back to over the wicket
Lalit Yadav to Rohit, FOUR, beautifully played, a low full-toss now, Rohit stays leg-sided and then serenely drives it through extra-cover, no need to run for those
Lalit Yadav to Rohit, 2 runs, flatter and at the stumps, whipped in front of square on the on-side, comes back for the second
Lalit Yadav to Rohit, no run, a full-toss and Rohit has missed out, finds cover with the drive and turns his head away in agony

Lalit Yadav to Rohit, FOUR, 15 off the over, Rohit shimmies down the pitch, gets close to the ball and then chips it back over the bowler's head, runs away to the ropes in a hurry, so are MI as they finish the batting PP at 75 for 0
1000+ runs against multiple opponents in the IPL David Warner vs PBKS & KKR Virat Kohli vs DC & CSK Rohit Sharma vs KKR & DC*
First time DC failed to pick a wicket inside PP this season
Powerplay scores for MI this IPL 2/52 vs GT 2/76 vs SRH 4/46 vs RR 0/75 vs DC*
Powerplay scores against DC this IPL 2/60 by PBKS 2/31 by RR 2/32 by CSK 1/88 by KKR 0/75 by MI*

Axar to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, the boundaries keep flowing - flighted delivery outside leg, Kishan gets down low, rolled his wrists ands then sweeps it backward of square on the on-side, beating the fielder in the deep
Axar to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, flatter and just outside off - chopped behind square on the off-side for a single
Axar to Rohit, no run, Axar tosses one on off, Rohit was looking to work it onto the on-side, closed the bat-face and the leading edge pops to the off-side
Axar to Rohit, no run, flighted delivery on off, Rohit comes down the wicket and then pushes it to the off-side
Axar to Rohit, no run, darted flatter and at the stumps - Rohit backs away on the cut and mistimes it to the off-side
Axar to Rohit, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Axar to Rohit, out Bowled!! Rohit falls one short of his fifty, but this is a badly needed wicket for DC. Axar kept it flatter and quicker as Rohit came down the pitch, the ball skids through and Rohit is undone by the length, plays all around and loses his off-stump. Thew key was the angle - Axar dragged the length back after that first-ball boundary, kept Rohit guessing and finally gets rid of him. They've taken the strategic break as well. Rohit b Axar 49(27) [4s-6 6s-3]
Rohit vs Axar Patel in IPL Balls: 69 Runs: 63 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 21.0 SR: 91.30 Dots: 28
Time for Anrich Nortje
Suryakumar Yadav, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Anrich Nortje, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Nortje to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, on a good length and at the stumps, nudged behind square on the on-side for a single

Nortje to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, appeal for LBW, but this was sliding down leg, could've been an inside edge as well - the inswinging yorker and Suryakumar Yadav played all around it, almost falling over in the process
Nortje to Suryakumar Yadav, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Nortje to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by (sub)Fraser-McGurk!! Wankhede has been silenced, a two-ball duck for Suryakumar Yadav and MI have lost two wickets on the bounce. Pitched up by Nortje and Suryakumar was shaping for the lofted drive - but his weight was on the back-foot and he inside halved the drive, popped in the air and Fraser-McGurk does well to back pedal and complete a two-handed overhead catch. Suryakumar Yadav c (sub)Fraser-McGurk b Nortje 0(2)
Nortje vs Suryakumar in IPL 15 balls 18 runs two dismissals
Hardik Pandya, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Nortje to Hardik Pandya, no run, a direct hit at the striker's end and Pandya would've joined Rohit and Surya in the dressing room - squirted a thick edge on the drive to backward point's left and set-off, the fielder was quick on the ball and then has a shy at the striker's end - Hardik was sent back, lost his poise and somehow tried to stumble back home - would've been short with a direct hit
Ishan Kishan vs Nortje in IPL (before today) Balls: 24 Runs: 56 no dismissal SR: 233.3 4s/6s: 7/3
Nortje to Hardik Pandya, 2 runs, fuller length delivery outside off, Hardik leans forward and then drives it crisply past cover, comes back for the second run

Nortje to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, tad fuller and at the stumps, Hardik leans into a straight-batted on-drive, to the left of mid-wicket who dives and gets a hand onto it, saving three runs in the process
Axar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, pushed into the gap past cover-point for a single
Axar to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, full-toss outside leg, Kishan was early into the drive and gets a leading edge that goes wide of the bowler
Axar to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, smashed, tossed up slower and wider of off - Hardik leans forward and then drives it crisply past cover, beating the fielder in the deep
Axar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, Axar drags the length back on off, Hardik plays late and edges it through slip for a single
Axar to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, pushed through by Axar - hacked down to long-on for a single
Axar to Hardik Pandya, no run, tossed up just outside off, steered straight to the fielder at backward point
Nortje to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the pads, whipped down to long leg for a single
Nortje to Hardik Pandya, no run, on a good length and just outside off, defended with an open face to the off-side
Nortje to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, cracking shot, banged in short by Nortje - Hardik stands tall, gets on top of the bounce and then clattersw the pull past mid-wicket for a boundary
Nortje to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, Nortje keeps it full and at the stumps, Hardik runs down the pitch and gets a thick edge on the drive, bounces well in front of the fielder in the deep at cover
Nortje to Ishan Kishan, SIX, massive, tad too short and Kishan is all over it like a rash - swivels across, picks the length and then dumps the pull, high and over backward square leg for a maximum

Nortje to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, a misunderstanding, Kishan nearly sold himself short, but he's saved as Axar fumbles - pushed in front of cover and he set-poff, so did Hardik Pandya, but both stuttered and stopped mid-way as Axar charged in - a clean pick-up and Kishan was in big trouble

Over summary 6-10 - Rohit smacks Lalit for 3 fours to end PP with a 15-run over - Axar pins Rohit on 49 and knocks him over eventually - Nortje stuns Wankhede as SKY mishits, out for a silver duck - Hardik gets going with a four, but Axar keeps it quiet - Nortje concedes four and six as MI play positive cricket

Axar to Ishan Kishan, SIX, that'll add salt to Axar's wounds - flighted delivery on middle and leg - Kishan bends down low and then swings it highh and over mid-wicket, went sailing a long way into the stands
Axar to Ishan Kishan, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Axar to Ishan Kishan, out Caught&Bowled!! That's a screamer and Axar has somehow caught it - dragged short and just outside off. Kishan rocked back and then thumped the pull, hard and flat, to the bowler's left - Axar nonchalantly plucked his left hand out and then holds on. He's chuffed to bits, Kishan looks in absolute disbelief, but he'll have to go. A big wicket, Kishan had just started to change gears. Ishan Kishan c and b Axar 42(23) [4s-4 6s-2]
Tilak Varma, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Axar to Tilak Varma, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, worked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Axar to Hardik Pandya, no run, pushed through on off, nudged to the right of cover-point, Tilak Varma was looking for a single and is sent back
Axar to Hardik Pandya, no run, flighted delivery on off, Pandya leans forward and gets an inside edge on the defensive push
Axar to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, Axar tosses one on off, punched into the gap square past point for a single
Jhye Richardson [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
J Richardson to Hardik Pandya, no run, on a good length and just outside off, Hardik scythes it hard and straight to the fielder at backward point
J Richardson to Hardik Pandya, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven straight to the fielder at cover
J Richardson to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, slower ball wide of off, Hardik reaches out and carves it past backward point for a single
J Richardson to Tilak Varma, FOUR, beautifully played, back of a length and around off, Tilak backs away, uses the pace on the ball and then beats backward point to his left with the cut
J Richardson to Tilak Varma, 1 run, Richardson goes full and at the stumps, pushed in front of mid-on for a single
J Richardson to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, very full from Richardson, Hardik toe-ends the drive in front of mid-wicket for a single
Khaleel, from round the wicket
Khaleel Ahmed [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Hardik Pandya, no run, fuller length delivery and angling into the pads, Hardik picks out mid-wicket with the flick
Khaleel Ahmed to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, Hardik went hard on the drive and mistimed it to the left of cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Tilak Varma, no run, on a good length and shaping back into the left-hander, tucked for room - Tilak drops it back at the bowler
Hardik vs Khaleel in IPL (before today) Balls: 21 Runs: 28 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 9.3 SR: 133.3
Khaleel Ahmed to Tilak Varma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Tilak Varma, out Caught by Axar!! Caught at backward point - short and wide of off, and Tilak couldn't resist the cut - went with hard hands and doesn't bother to keep it down. It's straight down Axar's throat and he ain't dropping any catches this afternoon. MI are scoring at a fast rate, but they're also losing wickets in the process. Tilak Varma c Axar b Khaleel Ahmed 6(5) [4s-1]
Khaleel vs Tilak Varma in IPL 7 balls 10 runs two dismissals
Tim David, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Khaleel Ahmed to Tim David, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven into the gap wide of cover for a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off, steered down towards third man for a single

J Richardson to Hardik Pandya, 2 runs, short of length outside off, steered wide of backward point and Khaleel from third man gets across and cuts it off with a slide, good effort to save two as that was travelling
J Richardson to Hardik Pandya, FOUR, half-volley outside off and that is in the slot, Hardik Pandya drives hard and wide of cover, raced away
J Richardson to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, slower ball leg-cutter full and wide outside off, Hardik Pandya reaches for it to drive to sweeper cover
J Richardson to Tim David, no run, short of length outside off , pushed straight to the fielder at cover
J Richardson to Tim David, no run, short of length on off, tight line and punched back
J Richardson to Tim David, 1 run, the attempted yorker is a low full-toss on the pads, flicked to deep backward square leg
Ishant Sharma [1.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Ishant to Tim David, 1 run, fullish outside off, slapped away to sweeper cover
Ishant to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Hardik Pandya mistimes the cut to backward point and takes a quick single
Ishant to Tim David, 1 run, short of length outside off, Tim David pulls to deep mid-wicket
Looks like the pitch has slowed down, both batters struggling for timing now.
Ishant to Hardik Pandya, no run, slower ball off-cutter full outside off, steered straight to the fielder at backward point
Pant changing the field. A delay.

Ishant to Hardik Pandya, 2 runs, slower ball full outside off, Hardik Pandya gets forward to drive wide of cover, Nortje gets across and cuts it off from sweeper cover, thuds the knee into the turf, takes a few chunks
Jhye Richardson is off the field, he is apparently struggling. It is very hot and humid out here.
Ishant to Hardik Pandya, 2 runs, a low full-toss on off, driven straight down the ground and the excellent Stubbs from long-on slides and saves two, superb stuff
Timeout! MI have slowed down but they are set to make over 175. The pitch too seems to be slowing up.

Over summary 11-15: - Axar takes a stunning return catch to dismiss a dangerous looking Ishan - Tilak gets going with a classy boundary - Tilak picks out fielder to perfection as Khaleel gets his first - Richardson and Ishant keep it tight as DC claw back
J Richardson to Tim David, SIX, slower ball full outside off, Tim David gets forward and lofts over wide long-on, did not get all of it, but he is a man-mountain, this Tim David
J Richardson to Tim David, no run, another slower ball full outside off, driven back and J Richardson gets a hand to stop it
J Richardson to Tim David, 1 run, low full-toss on the pads, flicked to deep square leg
J Richardson to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, slower ball full outside off, driven hard and straight to wide long-off
J Richardson to Tim David, 1 run, another low full-toss on the pads, flicked to deep square leg
J Richardson to Hardik Pandya, 2 wides, went for the yorker but slips it down leg, Hardik Pandya flicks and misses, Pant dives to his left to get a hand and save more runs
J Richardson to Tim David, 1 run, slower ball on a back of a length outside off, worked to deep mid-wicket
Khaleel Ahmed [3.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
J Richardson off the field. He clearly is struggling.

Khaleel Ahmed to Tim David, 3 runs, sloppy from DC. A slower ball off-cutter on a back of a length outside off, Tim David drags the pull wide of deep backward square leg and the throw comes to Pant who hits direct with Hardik Pandya in. The ricochet goes to long-on and David is not looking at the ball, has to put in the full-length dive to make it even as the throw is not fielded by the fielder. Two turns into three. Needless throw that from Pant. Half a chance though to run David out had the fielder collected and taken the stump off
Khaleel Ahmed to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, slower ball full and Hardik Pandya gets forward to drive to long-off
Khaleel Ahmed to Tim David, no run, slower ball full on off, driven straight to the fielder at cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Tim David, SIX, that's the power of Tim David. He picks the slower ball off-cutter from a length and mauls it over mid-wicket and he did not get all of it too
Khaleel Ahmed to Tim David, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, cut to sweeper cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Hardik Pandya, SIX, predictable stuff and Khaleel Ahmed travels. A slower ball full outside off, in the slot and Hardik Pandya gets forward to loft nicely over long-off
Anrich Nortje [2.0-0-17-1] is back into the attack
DC have made their impact sub - Khaleel Ahmed off and Kumar Kushagra in.
Nortje to Tim David, FOUR, slides into the pads, slower ball leg-cutter and short fine-leg was in, swiped away wide of him, poor ball and four
Nortje to Tim David, no ball, SIX, this is even worse from Nortje. A high full-toss, over the waist, slammed into the top tier at fine-leg, flew many a mile. SKY loves it
A free-hit now.
Nortje to Tim David, wide, the free-hit is a wide outside off, outside the tramline
Nortje to Tim David, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter dug in outside off, hit to long-on
Nortje to Hardik Pandya, wide, slower ball off-cutter outside off, is way outside off and another wide
Nortje to Hardik Pandya, no run, slower ball off-cutter dug in, Hardik Pandya tries to hit too hard, inside-edges it back to Pant
Nortje to Hardik Pandya, no run, this slower ball off-cutter outside off is working, dabbed to short third man and Tim David does not want the quick single
Nortje to Hardik Pandya, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Nortje to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by (sub)Fraser-McGurk!! Another underwhelming strike-rate for Hardik Pandya and he goes. A low full-toss on the pads, should have been sent into the stands, instead he finds deep backward square leg and the sub Fraser-McGurk makes no mistake with the reverse-cup. Hardik Pandya c (sub)Fraser-McGurk b Nortje 39(33) [4s-3 6s-1]
A wide called belatedly by umpire Kumar Dharmasena and DC have reviewed. It is a wide.
Romario Shepherd, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Nortje to Shepherd, wide, DC lose the review. The slower ball short outside off, is a tad too wide and Shepherd reaches for it to cut, misses, umpire Kumar Dharmasena gives the wide
Nortje to Shepherd, 1 run, full on the stumps, driven to long-off
Ishant Sharma [2.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Ishant to Shepherd, wide, dug in short outside off, too high and left alone to take the wide
Ishant to Shepherd, FOUR, full outside off, in the slot, driven hard and wide of cover, Ponting is not happy with the field placing, he makes his point known
Ishant to Shepherd, 1 run, good yorker outside off, dug out to the left of Ishant
Ishant to Tim David, wide, wide slower ball off-cutter outside off, very wide, another wide
Ishant to Tim David, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter dug in outside off, pulled hard and straight to deep square leg
Ishant to Shepherd, 1 run, good yorker length delivery on off, driven to long-off and Ishant is on the floor after delivering that

Ishant to Tim David, SIX, Ishant misses the yorker, it was the low full-toss on the body, flicked to deep backward square leg and Tim David has reviewed that for height, it is below the waist and MI lose the review
Ishant to Tim David, FOUR, slower ball short and wide outside off, Tim David crashes that wide of extra-cover and gives sweeper cover no chance. The power of the man
Nortje to Shepherd, FOUR, this man is another beast. A slower ball leg-cutter outside off, shortish and Shepherd has pumelled this straight down the ground, no chance for long-off and long-on

Nortje to Shepherd, SIX, what a blow. Fullish outside off, Shepherd leans back and gives it everything, a flat hit and it did not seem to have the legs to go all the way, but it flies into the crowd at long-on

Nortje to Shepherd, SIX, holy hell. Shepherd is turning it on. He shuffles across and it's full on off and middle, he flicks over deep square leg and it has gone out of the ground, Tim David and the MI team loved it, need another ball as this one has disappeared
Nortje to Shepherd, SIX, six more. A slower ball off-cutter dug in outside off, flat-batted cut over sweeper cover, pure muscle and power from the Guyana man-mountain

Nortje to Shepherd, FOUR, now the half-volley on the stumps, Shepherd drills it straight down the ground and again too much pace for long-off or long-on to get across and cut it off. What a cameo this is

Nortje to Shepherd, SIX, this over could be the difference between a win and a loss. A full delivery angling into leg-stump, Shepherd clears his front leg and helicopters that over wide long-on, perhaps the best ball of the over and that too has flown. 32 off the last over and Ishan and Pandya are all smiles. Sachin is clapping as well, meanwhile Shepherd and Tim David walk off with arms around their shoulders

17:15 Local Time, 11:45 GMT, 17:15 IST: Wow. Shepherd! He has come out of nowhere to slam a 10-ball 39. What an assault on Nortje in that last over. 32 off it and MI have posted an imposing 234. Rohit and Ishan set the tone earlier, especially the former. He batted as he always does - proactively in the powerplay. But Axar ended his innings on 49 and there was a streak of quick wickets which saw MI slip to 121/4 but Hardik promoting himself to 4 was joined by Tim David and they added another stand. And then the late heroics of Shepherd added the icing on the cake. That assault from Shepherd has provided MI with the cushion they need. A stiff chase ahead for DC. Can they get there? Back for the reply in 5 minutes...

Tim David: One went out of the ground and everyone in the stands enjoyed that. Great effort today, we had to stand up after a tough start to the season. Shepherd put the hammer down in that last over. Off pace deliveries didn't feel like bouncing up high. Perfect finish (last over) and we have got some momentum I thought I was going to die when that ball came towards me (high full toss off Nortje that he managed to hit for six).

Tim David at Wankhede in IPL Inns: 11 Runs: 288 Avg: 48.0 SR: 195.91
Welcome back. MI have their impact sub - SKY out and Madhwal in.
